'''格連·大衛·韋倫'''（{{lang-en|'''Glenn David Whelan'''}}，{{bd|1984年|1月13日|catIdx=Whelan, Glenn}}）是一名[[愛爾蘭共和國|愛爾蘭]]職業足球員，司職[[中場|正中場]]，現時效力[[英格蘭足球甲級聯賽|英甲]]球會[[弗利特伍德镇足球俱乐部|弗利特伍德]]，亦是[[愛爾蘭國家足球隊|愛爾蘭國家隊]]成員。

韋倫在[[曼彻斯特城足球俱乐部|曼城]]展開足球事業，但只曾於外借[[貝里足球俱樂部|貝利]]後在[[歐洲足協盃|歐洲足協盃]]為一隊上陣1次。他其後轉投[[谢周三足球俱乐部|錫周三]]，協助球隊於2005年升班[[英冠|英冠]]。2008年1月他以50萬[[英鎊|英鎊]]身價加盟[[斯托克城足球俱乐部|史篤城]]，又一次協助球隊取得升班[[英超|英超]]的資格。

==生平==

===球會===
<!--;曼城
Whelan started his career with [[Manchester_City_F.C.|Manchester City]] joining from Irish feeder club [[Cherry_Orchard_F.C.|Cherry Orchard]] in 2001.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/glenn-whelan-irishman-seeks-final-vindication-against-club-that-spurned-him-2283197.html|title=Glenn Whelan: Irishman seeks final vindication against club that spurned him|publisher=independent.co.uk | date=3 July 2011|location=London}}</ref> He made one solitary appearance in the [[UEFA_Europa_League|UEFA Cup]] coming on as a substitute for [[Paul_Bosvelt|Paul Bosvelt]] against [[The_New_Saints_F.C.|Total Network Solutions]] in August 2003,<ref>{{cite news | title =Man City sail through| publisher =BBC Sport| date =2003-08-28| url =http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/europe/3185429.stm| accessdate =2007-11-10 }}</ref> before joining [[Bury_F.C.|Bury]] on a one-month loan the following month.<ref>{{cite news| title =Bury bag Whelan| publisher =BBC Sport| date =2003-09-29| url =http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bury/3149572.stm| accessdate =2007-11-10 }}</ref> After appearing in the Republic of Ireland's [[2003_FIFA_World_Youth_Championship|World Youth Cup]] campaign in November and December, he returned to Bury on another one-month loan on 24 December 2003.<ref>{{cite news | title =Bury sign Whelan on loan| publisher =BBC Sport| date =2003-12-24| url =http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bury/3346075.stm| accessdate =2007-11-10 }}</ref>

;錫周三
Whelan joined Sheffield Wednesday on a free transfer in the summer of 2004.<ref>{{cite news | last = Johnson| first = William| coauthors = | title =Premiership transfers | publisher =''Daily Telegraph'' | date =2004-07-21 | url =http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/main.jhtml?xml=/sport/2004/07/21/sfntra21.xml&page=2 | accessdate =2008-02-01 | location=London}}</ref> He was vital in securing a play-off place for the club, starting a total of 41 games and scoring four goals. Whelan was voted "[[man_of_the_match|man of the match]]" in the League One play-off final against [[Hartlepool_United_F.C.|Hartlepool United]] at the [[Millennium_Stadium|Millennium Stadium]] in [[Cardiff|Cardiff]] after scoring the game-winning third goal for Wednesday.<ref>{{cite news |title=Hartlepool vs Sheffield Wed|url=http://www.swfc.co.uk/page/MatchReport/0,,10304~29173,00.html|publisher=swfc.co.uk |accessdate=5 July 2011 }}</ref>

After Wednesday won promotion to the Championship Whelan was trialled as captain by [[Paul_Sturrock|Paul Sturrock]] after club captain [[Lee_Bullen|Lee Bullen]] was injured. Wednesday went on to successfully consolidate themselves in the Championship during the 2005–06 season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Whelan targets Owls consolidation|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/s/sheff_wed/4198834.stm|publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=5 July 2011|first=Jonathan|last=Rawcliffe|date=2005-09-03}}</ref>

In July 2006, Whelan was placed on the transfer list by Sturrock following increased competition for places in the Wednesday midfield after the arrival of [[Wade_Small|Wade Small]], [[Kenny_Lunt|Kenny Lunt]] and [[Yoann_Folly|Yoann Folly]].<ref>{{cite news | title =Owls bag Saints midfielder Folly | publisher =BBC Sport | date =2006-07-12 | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/s/sheff_wed/5168666.stm| accessdate =2008-02-25  }}</ref> He was subsequently removed from the transfer list by the following manager [[Brian_Laws|Brian Laws]].<ref>{{cite news | title =Owls enter Whelan contract talks | publisher =BBC Sport | date =2007-06-26 | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/s/sheff_wed/6240988.stm| accessdate =2008-02-25  }}</ref> Whelan repaid the faith shown in him with seven goals, most notably "screamers" against Leicester, Southampton & Luton. He then went on to win a number of 'Player of the year' awards for the club's 2006–07 season.<ref>{{cite news| title =Whelan Bags Award | publisher =Vital Network | date =2007-04-20 | url =http://www.sheffwed.vitalfootball.co.uk/article.asp?a=62061 |accessdate =2008-02-25 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| title =Whelan Bags Owls Gong | work = | publisher =Vital Network | date =2007-04-26 | url =http://www.sheffwed.vitalfootball.co.uk/article.asp?a=62876 | accessdate =2008-02-25 }}</ref> Sheffield Wednesday rejected bids for Whelan from both [[Burnley_F.C.|Burnley]] and [[Plymouth_Argyle_F.C.|Plymouth Arygle]] in January 2008.<ref>{{cite news|title=Owls reject Burnley's Whelan bid|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/s/sheff_wed/7180911.stm|publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=5 July 2011|date=2008-01-10}}</ref> However a £500,000 bid from Stoke City was accepted on transfer deadline day.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.swfc.co.uk/page/News/0,,10304~1230543,00.html|title=Kavanagh Returns As Whelan Leaves|publisher=swfc.co.uk| accessdate=5 May 2011}}</ref>
-->
;史篤城
2008年2月1日，[[英冠|英冠]]球會史篤城以50萬[[英鎊|英鎊]]從同是[[英冠|英冠]]的錫周三購入韋倫並簽署合約三年半<ref>{{cite news|language=en|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/s/stoke_city/7221201.stm|title=Stoke sign Whelan and Gallagher|publisher=''[[BBC_Sport|BBC Sport]]''|date=2008-02-01|accessdate=2013-06-12|archive-date=2020-04-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200418032406/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/s/stoke_city/7221201.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2009年9月15日，韋倫與史篤城簽署一份新的四年合約，留隊至2013年夏季<ref>{{cite news |language=en |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/s/stoke_city/8257649.stm |title=Whelan signs four-year Stoke deal |publisher=''[[BBC_Sport|BBC Sport]]'' |date=2009-09-15 |accessdate=2013-06-12 |archive-date=2020-04-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200418032411/http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/s/stoke_city/8257649.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2012年1月11日，韋倫與史篤城簽署一份新的三年半合約，另球會有選擇權可延長多一年<ref>{{cite news |language=en |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/glenn-whelan-signs-new-stoke-deal-6288103.html |title=Glenn Whelan signs new Stoke deal |publisher=''The Independent'' |date=2012-01-11 |accessdate=2013-06-12 |archive-date=2020-04-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200418032418/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/glenn-whelan-signs-new-stoke-deal-6288103.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

